    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `set foldmethod=expr foldexpr=v:lua.vim.treesitter.foldexpr()`, there can be an \"attempt to index a nil value\" error.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nFirst, create a session that shows two different markdown files in vertical split. For example, from the root of this repo:\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\n2. `:e BUILD.md`\n3. `:wincmd v`\n4.  `:e CONTRIBUTING.md`\n5. `:mksession`\n\nTo reproduce the error:\n\n1. Create the following 'init.lua':\n\n    ```lua\n    vim.cmd('au FileType markdown set foldmethod=expr foldexpr=v:lua.vim.treesitter.foldexpr()')\n\n    -- `vim.schedule_wrap()` is important\n    local force_ft = vim.schedule_wrap(function(ev) vim.bo[ev.buf].filetype = vim.bo[ev.buf].filetype end)\n    vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', { once = true, pattern = 'markdown', callback = force_ft })\n    ```\n\n2. `nvim --clean -u init.lua`\n3. `:source Session.vim`. This results in the following error:\n\n    ```\n    vim.schedule callback: ...OnpB/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_fold.lua:456: attempt to index a nil value\n    stack traceback:\n            ...OnpB/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_fold.lua:456: in function 'callback'\n            ...OnpB/usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_fold.lua:194: in function 'cb'\n            ...r/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/languagetree.lua:544: in function '_run_async_callbacks'\n            ...r/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/languagetree.lua:600: in function <...r/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/languagetree.lua:579>\n    ```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo error when using properly set up tree-sitter folding.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-2689+g929f03fa8c but can be reproduced on 0.11.3 also\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo, doesn't have this functionality\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64, 6.19.9-arch1-1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.3.1-arch1\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nAppimage",
