        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "schedule_wrap is a sign of a race condition. Looks like [`foldinfos[bufnr]` returns nil](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/10ca09a2cbe4546a67cfc2ca99eed806077416a5/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_fold.lua#L456), and involves  `get_parser`: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/10ca09a2cbe4546a67cfc2ca99eed806077416a5/runtime/lua/vim/treesitter/_fold.lua#L30-L34\n\nso this indeed seems related to https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/fd1e019e90e76bb3f6236210ac6287f3b8d4d47f , though that commit isn't at fault, but this just points to a need to avoid the race in `_fold.lua`\n\ncc @ribru17 ",
